      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When <foreign xml:lang="ta">n</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">m</foreign> occur as initials of the coming words, <foreign xml:lang="ta">aintu</foreign> ' five '</l>
<l>and <foreign xml:lang="ta">mūṉṟu</foreign> ' three ' have the consonants [<foreign xml:lang="ta">n</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ</foreign>] according to</l>
<l>the initials [ of the coming words].<note place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">aintu + nāḻi &gt; aiññāḻi</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="ta">mūṉru + maṇṭai &gt; mummaṇṭai.</foreign></note></l>
